{
    "type": "random",
    "message": ["While there can a lot of work you have to do as a CS major, is this work something you enjoy or something you always dread?", 
                "CS can be stressful, but there's a number of things you can do to reduce this stress such as not taking too many CS classes at once, not overwhelming yourself with extracurriculars, and making time for yourself to relax.", 
                "If you're worried about being overwhelmed by CS reach out to your professors and peer advisors to see how much time you'll need to put into each class so you can schedule accordingly."]
}

{
    "type": "random",
    "message": ["Try taking a few CS classes like Intro to Java and Data Structures to see if you like it!", 
                "Talk to your professors and other people you know involved in the major and see what like about what they do to decide if it's for you or not.", 
                "Think about what got you into CS in the first place. Is that something that still inspires you? What do you want to do with a CS major? Go into industry? Do research?"]
}

{
    "type": "random",
    "message": ["Most students usualy take Intro to AI their sophomore or junior year.", 
                "Before taking Intro to AI you must take to Intro to Java (or AP CS A) and Intro to Data Structures. After those you can take Intro to AI!", 
                "Intro to AI is a requirement for all other AI classes in the AI depth track so take it as early as you can, but don't take too many CS classes at once because it'll be a very stressful semester."]
}
